Sportsmail understands that a patrol from Control Event Solutions have been sent to Di Maria’s house for a week at least while security at the premises is beefed up.

The Manchester United star was the victim of a terrifying raid  when burglars are believed to have used scaffolding poles to smash their way in to his home.

Three thieves used the metal poles to break through patio doors as the Argentina winger reportedly ate dinner with wife Jorgelina Cardoso and one-year-old daughter Mia at his Cheshire mansion.

The break-in occurred at 7.30pm, just hours after the 26-year-old starred for United in their 3-1 win over Leicester City at Old Trafford in the Barclays Premier League.

Di Maria and his family were  whisked away by United's security team and later taken to a hotel by police, according to The Sun.

